This paper deals with the coverage of a mobile sensor network, which is a topic that falls under the category of Networking and Internet Architecture (cs.NI). The paper also discusses the movement of sensors and intruders, which is related to Robotics (cs.RO). The characterization of area coverage and time durations involves the use of algorithms and data structures, which are topics in Data Structures and Algorithms (cs.DS). The game theoretic approach used to derive optimal mobility strategies for sensors and intruders falls under the category of Systems and Control (cs.SY). Finally, the paper discusses the use of mobility to improve coverage, which is a topic in Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI).
